OL,7,FIn a statement read out to the court,
OL,8,Fthe first victim's father said his son
OL,9,Fhad been "smart, kind and considerate"
OL,10,Fbut fell victim to "feeding (Fuge's)
OL,11,Ftwisted need for control".
OL,13,FHe said his son was was bullied in
OL,14,Fschool but also intimidated at home -
OL,15,Fwhere he should have felt safe - by
OL,16,FFuge's online presence "prowling just
OL,17,Fout of reach".
